        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 10:37PM CDT by NWS Hastings NE</headline>
        <description>At 1036 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Hunter, or 18 miles southwest of Beloit, that
were nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Victor, Hunter, and Tipton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
